transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I need to cancel my next prescription, my wife, I bought some about almost six monthsâ€”

Speaker 2: Ago when they posted me back in six months, and I'm telling you the first one.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: One second.

Speaker 1: Is your name Mark?

Speaker 2: Mark, yes.

Speaker 1: She's come down with breast cancer and she just hasn't had the time.

Speaker 2: Oh, I'm sorry to hear that, sir.

Speaker 1: I mean, you know, we can push it out another six months from today and give you some time.

Speaker 2: No, just cancel.

Speaker 1: If I need it, I'll just call you all back again.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but there won't be a prescription in the future if you want to do that.

Speaker 1: That's why, you know, we try to postpone it for you.

Speaker 2: No, you just cancel it.

Speaker 1: And you do realize you won't be able to reorder it, correct?

Speaker 2: Yes, correct.

Speaker 1: All right, sir.

Speaker 2: We'll take care of it for you.

Speaker 1: Anything else?

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: I thought I did, but I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.
